result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Colt M Voge was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (1st). This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Payable at the rate of $50.00 per month, starting on or before January 1, 2016 and on the same day each month thereafter, until paid in full.  $15.00 payment plan fee added.    Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.

records.addlTxt: ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Poss.  Plead no contest to counts 1 and 3.  Proposed diversion agreement on count 1.   Counts 2 and 4 and 15CM81 dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.    Court advised the charges and possible penalties of the counts he plead to. He understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood. Court reviewed the diversion agreement and it's requirements with the defendant.  Defendant stated that he understood and can comply with the requirements.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the pleas.  Found guilty of count 3.  Finding of guilt withheld on count 1.  Diversion agreement approved as to count 1.  Joint recommendation for  $887.50 on count 3.  Minimum revocation.  Court ordered:  fine of $887.50.  Payable at the rate of $50/mo, starting 1/1/16.    Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.  6 month DL revocation.  Credit for time already served.  Alc assmt.
